post_text:
With the approval of the Board of Education, On Wednesday, September 9, 2020 as part of the Capital Project, a contractor will be onsite applying a herbicide for broadleaf weed control. The chemical that will be used is Speedzone.

As required, the contractor will be using yellow placard cards as a notification to stay off the fields. While the timeline for personal use to remain off the fields is 24 hours, regulations for school districts are 72 hours.

Out of an abundance of caution all affected fields, track and tennis courts will be closed from Wednesday September 9, 2020 through Sunday September 13, 2020.

These areas will reopen on Monday September 14, 2020.

Good morning!

We are distributing Chromebooks next week to students in grades 6-12. This will be a curbside pickup similar to when Chromebooks were dropped off in June. We ask you to fill out the Technology Loan Agreement Form before coming to campus.
https://drive.google.com/file/d/11-F8SiST_IoI7gUVM8081cG6_M5PF2zi/view?usp=sharing

9/2/20 - 3:00 pm - 6:00 pm
9/3/20 - 9:00 am - 2:00 pm
9/4/20 - 7:00 am -11:00 am

During your pick-up, please wear a facemask.

On another note, thank you for your patience with schedules as we have been working to have them fit our hybrid model for reopening. They will be viewable in the parent portal early next week.

Please reach out if you have any questions.

Have a great weekend!

Matt Ward

post_text:
Parents' Decisions for the 2020-2021 School Year -
In order to create class lists, restructure room utilization, and disburse resources equitably, the District is collecting parents' formal decisions about the upcoming school year regarding in-person instruction (for gr. K-5), hybrid instruction (for gr. 6-12), or remote learning. Additionally, the District is collecting parents' decisions regarding transportation on the school bus.

We encourage parents to complete this survey as soon as they feel prepared, but no later than August 11th. We understand that this is a difficult decision, but the sooner GCS has the information, the better we can plan for our students. We ask that if you have multiple children, please complete and submit the form for each child separately by selecting ""submit another response." Thank you.

https://forms.gle/UuzxAXrTtQdtCygr5

post_text:
Fall Sports to Begin September 21st
As of right today, New York State Public High School Athletic Association decided that Fall sports will now begin on September 21, 2020. With this change in starting date, registration for Fall sports will open in FamilyID on August 21, 2020 for Varsity, JV & modified athletes.

The district encourages parents to take their child for an annual physical. If you are unable to get an appointment with your primary care physician, please contact Nurse Mackey.

For parents of, already identified, student-athletes taking part in the Athletic Placement Process (APP), fitness testing will take place closer to the week of September 14th.

post_text:
It is with great honor that we share with you what both the Visual Arts & Music Departments K-12 at Greenville Central School District have been up to. Due to our unusual circumstance, the students could not take part in any spring music performances, plays, or visual art shows; and they thought it would be a fantastic idea to create a virtual space in order to give recognition to all of their hard work. Enjoy!

https://gcsdartsamazingathome.weebly.com/

post_text:
Wednesday May 27 Virtual Field Trip Part 2
Today's second trip is a choral performance directed by Mr. Meredith. Well done musicians!
From Mr. Meredith:
"I'm proud to present the Greenville combined HS chorus performance of "Omnia Sol." Each year at our final concert we sing this piece as a send-off song for our graduating seniors. The seniors sing the opening verse, the underclassmen sing the second, and they combine for the refrain. Each student recorded their voice independently, and they have been united for this final performance. Thank you to all the students who participated; a special congratulations to all our senior chorus members."
https://youtu.be/La2ddzfEyAA

post_text:
Museums are challenging people to recreate a work of art using only people and/or objects found around their homes. The stay-at-home orders during the COVID-19 pandemic have made everyone more acquainted with their living spaces than they ever thought they would be and a little silly.
Greenville School District is jumping on the trend! Here are some examples created by GCS faculty.
Let's all celebrate and make art together from our homes. Give this a try and feel free to share it with me or tag GCSartroom on Instagram! See what recreations people all over have done at The Getty, #betweenartandquarantine, and #tussenkunstenquarantaine.
